statement.title: # Content
statement.content:
If we sum up every digit of a number and the result can be exactly divided by $10$, we say this number is a good number.

You are required to count the number of good numbers in the range from $A$ to $B$, inclusive.

statement.title: # Standard Input
statement.content:
The first line has a number $T$ ($T\leq 10000$) , indicating the number of test cases.

Each test case comes with a single line with two numbers $A$ and $B$ ($0 \leq A \leq B \leq 10^{18}$).

statement.title: # Standard Output
statement.content: For test case $X$, output `Case #X: ` first, then output the number of good numbers in a single line.

statement.title: # Samples
statement.content:
Input Output
2 1 10 1 20Case #1: 0 Case #2: 1

statement.title: # Note
statement.content: The answer maybe very large, we recommend you to use long long instead of int.
